      "date": "2011-03-01 04:03:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI thin kthis is the wrong approach.\nLustre must totally ensure that the locking is consistent internally and as such whatever locking is there in VFS should not conflict.\nAt most we can do an LBUG or a nasty CERROR if there is a disagreement between vfs and ldlm about a locking issue.\n\nPatch for the specific failure you are referring to is available in lustre bugzilla bug 22040",
